✈️Pika World Update – 28 Jan 2022✈️Equity markets continued to slide further as interest rate hike expectations weighed on risk-on sentiments. There isn’t much positive news around the market  given that many corporations drove the idea of supply chain constraints affecting their performance.🗽Apple: Shining once more🍎Shares of Apple in after-hours trading rose sharply as it reported a robust set of results for the December quarter  smashing targets. All business segments except for iPad saw growth. The services segment was the star as it is up 23.8% from last year  well ahead of expectation.While the company cited supply chain constraints  it is mainly on old legacy chips. Thus  analysts expect Apple to continue its drive momentum against a more uncertain macro environment.📱Robinhood Markets: A poor showing🧸Shares of Robinhood fell sharply after its first-quarter revenue dropped 35%  a stark contrast from its peak performance a year ago. The wider than expected loss also add worry to the company performance. Much of this loss is attributed to share-based compensation.The company struggled to attract more users to its platform after losing around 100 000 customers in the third quarter. Given the die down of the meme vibe and a weaker crypto trading environment  the company continued to be hurt by a general  more fragile trading environment.Pika World will be taking losses on the position and reducing exposure.💈Mastercard and Visa🏸Both companies reported decent results  but Wall Street seems to ask for more. Mastercard beats estimates by 6%  but this wasn’t good enough. The 2022 full-year revenue guidance is also on a disappointing note. The market expects a 20% growth compared to its estimated high-teens forecast.On the flip side  Visa first-quarter result beats estimate and showed strong performance in the e-commerce transaction sphere  given a healthier cross border travel activity in a recovering economy.The market continued to be in limbo  and we expect more downside risk as the participants re-adjust their expectations and adapt to a less accommodative environment. It is a painful journey for Pika Nat  too  building on a more defensive mode.It is 28 Jan  Friday  9 am in Singapore and 9 pm in New York.Pika World wishes all friends a safe and re-charging weekend!

As a result  all significant indexes rose with Russell 2000 shinning after periods of underperformamce.Markets participants are adjusting to the possibility that the Fed may not be as hawkish as many would expect after many FOMC members spoke about a more data-driven approach in their monetary stance.🪜Alphabet: The moon is here🚀The company smashed expectations and announced a 20-for-one stock split  which spurs the stock to rise sharply after-hours. Despite supply constraints  substantial advertising revenue coupled with record sales for their Pixel phones helps brighten the risk-on sentiments.Cloud business showed strength. Given the split nature of the stock  it may appeal to participants who generally love such trade. Pika World will be on the sideline unless there is an opportunity.🧨Paypal: A disappointing quarter⛽️The company guidance lack conviction  and it is down more than 10% in after-hour. This is by far the most significant burden in the Pika World portfolio  and we are considering shedding the positions as we move to a more defensive mood.The CEO discussed the weaker guidance due to the amplified effect on Omicron on cross border businesses and hit primarily on SMEs. Without the revenue from eBay  investors’ patience are thinning on how the CEO can transform the company back to a power pack growth mode.🚘General Motors: Poor guidance🏀While the company announced better than expected fourth-quarter results  its mixed bag outlook dampened sentiments. As a result  shares are slightly weaker in after-hour trading. Nonetheless  investors are warming to the idea of a conservative outlook by GM as the EV transformation story unfolds.Semiconductor shortage continued to be the main reason for the company’s outlook. Still  with the consumer strength remaining firm  it is hopeful that they could hit the upper range of their guidance despite the headwinds such as chips shortage  commodity prices increase a higher interest rates environment.Pika World will be on the sideline at the moment.💻AMD: The sky is clear🛎Shares popped higher with a forecast that blew the minds of analysts. Each of their businesses is doing well  and revenue from the data centre doubles yearly. In addition  the growing adoption of their EPYC processors in cloud platforms among enterprise customers delivered strong results.The company expects to deliver another solid year as they ramp up on their existing strength and set sight to launch the next generation of their products in the area of PC  Gaming and Data centre. A higher than expected gross margin also reflected the company’s ability to control cost and a rich product mix that helps to sustain healthy growth.It is 2 Feb  Wednesday  8.10 am in Singapore and 8.10 pm in New York.Pika World wishes everyone a prosperous day ahead!Cheers Pika Nat.

💎Pika World Update 3 February 2022💎🧨Meta: Poor Guidance🧯The shares plunged in after-hours after weaker than expected earnings. Guidance is also soft  with first-quarter revenue expected to grow around 3% to 11%. The headwinds lie in Apple’s iOS mobile software changes  making targeting users more challenging than before.The “metaverse” venture reported an operating loss of $3.3 billion. Pika World will be exploring an entry point given the pullback but cautioned progressive built up.⌛️Paypal: Concerns rising⛏Pika World reduced a large part of the holdings as the stock sank into free fall. The new re-assessment of the company points to some alarming trends. While it expects to add around 15 to 20 million unique users in 2022  this is a fall from 48.9 million in 2021.Instead of growing the user base  the company is not focusing on increasing revenue per active account. As a result  the stock is likely to be under pressure until growth accelerates again or when investors feel that its forecasts are perhaps too conservative.📱Spotify: Poor earnings📽The stock had a rough start after the guidance for the first quarter led to a slowdown in subscriber growth. Nevertheless  it added around 3 million new premium subscribers  a mild increase of 1.7%.Spotify has been posing losses on a per-share basis for most quarters ever since it is listed. Losses had narrowed  but the guidance haunted risk-on sentiments. With slower growth  the company has to look to advertisement for more revenue  and some have pointed the business into a radio station nature than a fast-growing subscription business.It is 3 February  Thursday  8.25 am in Singapore and 8.25 pm in New York.The market is back on a rough ride  and Pika World wishes all friends a fruitful day ahead!Cheers Pika Nat.
